2240/* Internal variable for sched_analyze_[12] () functions.
2241 If it is nonzero, this means that sched_analyze_[12] looks
2242 at the most toplevel SET. */
2243static bool can_start_lhs_rhs_p;
2244
2245/* Extend reg info for the deps context DEPS given that
2246 we have just generated a register numbered REGNO. */
2247static void
2248extend_deps_reg_info (struct deps_desc *deps, int regno)
2249{
2250 int max_regno = regno + 1;
2251
2252 gcc_assert (!reload_completed);
2253
2254 /* In a readonly context, it would not hurt to extend info,
2255 but it should not be needed. */
2256 if (reload_completed && deps->readonly)
2257 {
2258 deps->max_reg = max_regno;
2259 return;
2260 }
2261
2262 if (max_regno > deps->max_reg)
2263 {
2264 deps->reg_last = XRESIZEVEC (struct deps_reg, deps->reg_last,
2265 max_regno);
2266 memset (&deps->reg_last[deps->max_reg],
2267 0, (max_regno - deps->max_reg)
2268 * sizeof (struct deps_reg));
2269 deps->max_reg = max_regno;
2270 }
2271}
2272
2273/* Extends REG_INFO_P if needed. */
2274void
2275maybe_extend_reg_info_p (void)
2276{
2277 /* Extend REG_INFO_P, if needed. */
2278 if ((unsigned int)max_regno - 1 >= reg_info_p_size)
2279 {
2280 size_t new_reg_info_p_size = max_regno + 128;
2281
2282 gcc_assert (!reload_completed && sel_sched_p ());
2283
2284 reg_info_p = (struct reg_info_t *) xrecalloc (reg_info_p,
2285 new_reg_info_p_size,
2286 reg_info_p_size,
2287 sizeof (*reg_info_p));
2288 reg_info_p_size = new_reg_info_p_size;
2289 }
2290}
2291
2292/* Analyze a single reference to register (reg:MODE REGNO) in INSN.
2293 The type of the reference is specified by REF and can be SET,
2294 CLOBBER, PRE_DEC, POST_DEC, PRE_INC, POST_INC or USE. */
2295
2296static void
2297sched_analyze_reg (struct deps_desc *deps, int regno, machine_mode mode,
2298 enum rtx_code ref, rtx_insn *insn)
2299{
2300 /* We could emit new pseudos in renaming. Extend the reg structures. */
2301 if (!reload_completed && sel_sched_p ()
2302 && (regno >= max_reg_num () - 1 || regno >= deps->max_reg))
2303 extend_deps_reg_info (deps, regno);
2304
2305 maybe_extend_reg_info_p ();
2306
2307 /* A hard reg in a wide mode may really be multiple registers.
2308 If so, mark all of them just like the first. */
2309 if (regno < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER)
2310 {
2311 int i = hard_regno_nregs[regno][mode];
2312 if (ref == SET)
2313 {
2314 while (--i >= 0)
2315 note_reg_set (regno + i);
2316 }
2317 else if (ref == USE)
2318 {
2319 while (--i >= 0)
2320 note_reg_use (regno + i);
2321 }
2322 else
2323 {
2324 while (--i >= 0)
2325 note_reg_clobber (regno + i);
2326 }
2327 }
2328
2329 /* ??? Reload sometimes emits USEs and CLOBBERs of pseudos that
2330 it does not reload. Ignore these as they have served their
2331 purpose already. */
2332 else if (regno >= deps->max_reg)
2333 {
2334 enum rtx_code code = GET_CODE (PATTERN (insn));
2335 gcc_assert (code == USE || code == CLOBBER);
2336 }
2337
2338 else
2339 {
2340 if (ref == SET)
2341 note_reg_set (regno);
2342 else if (ref == USE)
2343 note_reg_use (regno);
2344 else
2345 note_reg_clobber (regno);
2346
2347 /* Pseudos that are REG_EQUIV to something may be replaced
2348 by that during reloading. We need only add dependencies for
2349 the address in the REG_EQUIV note. */
2350 if (!reload_completed && get_reg_known_equiv_p (regno))
2351 {
2352 rtx t = get_reg_known_value (regno);
2353 if (MEM_P (t))
2354 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (t, 0), insn);
2355 }
2356
2357 /* Don't let it cross a call after scheduling if it doesn't
2358 already cross one. */
2359 if (REG_N_CALLS_CROSSED (regno) == 0)
2360 {
2361 if (!deps->readonly && ref == USE && !DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
2362 deps->sched_before_next_call
2363 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, deps->sched_before_next_call);
2364 else
2365 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_function_call, 1,
2366 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
2367 }
2368 }
2369}
2370
2371/* Analyze a single SET, CLOBBER, PRE_DEC, POST_DEC, PRE_INC or POST_INC
2372 rtx, X, creating all dependencies generated by the write to the
2373 destination of X, and reads of everything mentioned. */
2374
2375static void
2376sched_analyze_1 (struct deps_desc *deps, rtx x, rtx_insn *insn)
2377{
2378 rtx dest = XEXP (x, 0);
2379 enum rtx_code code = GET_CODE (x);
2380 bool cslr_p = can_start_lhs_rhs_p;
2381
2382 can_start_lhs_rhs_p = false;
2383
2384 gcc_assert (dest);
2385 if (dest == 0)
2386 return;
2387
2388 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->start_lhs)
2389 sched_deps_info->start_lhs (dest);
2390
2391 if (GET_CODE (dest) == PARALLEL)
2392 {
2393 int i;
2394
2395 for (i = XVECLEN (dest, 0) - 1; i >= 0; i--)
2396 if (XEXP (XVECEXP (dest, 0, i), 0) != 0)
2397 sched_analyze_1 (deps,
2398 gen_rtx_CLOBBER (VOIDmode,
2399 XEXP (XVECEXP (dest, 0, i), 0)),
2400 insn);
2401
2402 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_lhs)
2403 sched_deps_info->finish_lhs ();
2404
2405 if (code == SET)
2406 {
2407 can_start_lhs_rhs_p = cslr_p;
2408
2409 sched_analyze_2 (deps, SET_SRC (x), insn);
2410
2411 can_start_lhs_rhs_p = false;
2412 }
2413
2414 return;
2415 }
2416
2417 while (GET_CODE (dest) == STRICT_LOW_PART || GET_CODE (dest) == SUBREG
2418 || GET_CODE (dest) == ZERO_EXTRACT)
2419 {
2420 if (GET_CODE (dest) == STRICT_LOW_PART
2421 || GET_CODE (dest) == ZERO_EXTRACT
2422 || df_read_modify_subreg_p (dest))
2423 {
2424 /* These both read and modify the result. We must handle
2425 them as writes to get proper dependencies for following
2426 instructions. We must handle them as reads to get proper
2427 dependencies from this to previous instructions.
2428 Thus we need to call sched_analyze_2. */
2429
2430 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (dest, 0), insn);
2431 }
2432 if (GET_CODE (dest) == ZERO_EXTRACT)
2433 {
2434 /* The second and third arguments are values read by this insn. */
2435 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (dest, 1), insn);
2436 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (dest, 2), insn);
2437 }
2438 dest = XEXP (dest, 0);
2439 }
2440
2441 if (REG_P (dest))
2442 {
2443 int regno = REGNO (dest);
2444 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (dest);
2445
2446 sched_analyze_reg (deps, regno, mode, code, insn);
2447
2448#ifdef STACK_REGS
2449 /* Treat all writes to a stack register as modifying the TOS. */
2450 if (regno >= FIRST_STACK_REG && regno <= LAST_STACK_REG)
2451 {
2452 /* Avoid analyzing the same register twice. */
2453 if (regno != FIRST_STACK_REG)
2454 sched_analyze_reg (deps, FIRST_STACK_REG, mode, code, insn);
2455
2456 add_to_hard_reg_set (&implicit_reg_pending_uses, mode,
2457 FIRST_STACK_REG);
2458 }
2459#endif
2460 }
2461 else if (MEM_P (dest))
2462 {
2463 /* Writing memory. */
2464 rtx t = dest;
2465
2466 if (sched_deps_info->use_cselib)
2467 {
2468 machine_mode address_mode = get_address_mode (dest);
2469
2470 t = shallow_copy_rtx (dest);
2471 cselib_lookup_from_insn (XEXP (t, 0), address_mode, 1,
2472 GET_MODE (t), insn);
2473 XEXP (t, 0)
2474 = cselib_subst_to_values_from_insn (XEXP (t, 0), GET_MODE (t),
2475 insn);
2476 }
2477 t = canon_rtx (t);
2478
2479 /* Pending lists can't get larger with a readonly context. */
2480 if (!deps->readonly
2481 && ((deps->pending_read_list_length + deps->pending_write_list_length)
2482 >= MAX_PENDING_LIST_LENGTH))
2483 {
2484 /* Flush all pending reads and writes to prevent the pending lists
2485 from getting any larger. Insn scheduling runs too slowly when
2486 these lists get long. When compiling GCC with itself,
2487 this flush occurs 8 times for sparc, and 10 times for m88k using
2488 the default value of 32. */
2489 flush_pending_lists (deps, insn, false, true);
2490 }
2491 else
2492 {
2493 rtx_insn_list *pending;
2494 rtx_expr_list *pending_mem;
2495
2496 pending = deps->pending_read_insns;
2497 pending_mem = deps->pending_read_mems;
2498 while (pending)
2499 {
2500 if (anti_dependence (pending_mem->element (), t)
2501 && ! sched_insns_conditions_mutex_p (insn, pending->insn ()))
2502 note_mem_dep (t, pending_mem->element (), pending->insn (),
2503 DEP_ANTI);
2504
2505 pending = pending->next ();
2506 pending_mem = pending_mem->next ();
2507 }
2508
2509 pending = deps->pending_write_insns;
2510 pending_mem = deps->pending_write_mems;
2511 while (pending)
2512 {
2513 if (output_dependence (pending_mem->element (), t)
2514 && ! sched_insns_conditions_mutex_p (insn, pending->insn ()))
2515 note_mem_dep (t, pending_mem->element (),
2516 pending->insn (),
2517 DEP_OUTPUT);
2518
2519 pending = pending->next ();
2520 pending_mem = pending_mem-> next ();
2521 }
2522
2523 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_pending_memory_flush, 1,
2524 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
2525 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->pending_jump_insns, 1,
2526 REG_DEP_CONTROL, true);
2527
2528 if (!deps->readonly)
2529 add_insn_mem_dependence (deps, false, insn, dest);
2530 }
2531 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (dest, 0), insn);
2532 }
2533
2534 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_lhs)
2535 sched_deps_info->finish_lhs ();
2536
2537 /* Analyze reads. */
2538 if (GET_CODE (x) == SET)
2539 {
2540 can_start_lhs_rhs_p = cslr_p;
2541
2542 sched_analyze_2 (deps, SET_SRC (x), insn);
2543
2544 can_start_lhs_rhs_p = false;
2545 }
2546}
2547
2548/* Analyze the uses of memory and registers in rtx X in INSN. */
2549static void
2550sched_analyze_2 (struct deps_desc *deps, rtx x, rtx_insn *insn)
2551{
2552 int i;
2553 int j;
2554 enum rtx_code code;
2555 const char *fmt;
2556 bool cslr_p = can_start_lhs_rhs_p;
2557
2558 can_start_lhs_rhs_p = false;
2559
2560 gcc_assert (x);
2561 if (x == 0)
2562 return;
2563
2564 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->start_rhs)
2565 sched_deps_info->start_rhs (x);
2566
2567 code = GET_CODE (x);
2568
2569 switch (code)
2570 {
2571 CASE_CONST_ANY:
2572 case SYMBOL_REF:
2573 case CONST:
2574 case LABEL_REF:
2575 /* Ignore constants. */
2576 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2577 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2578
2579 return;
2580
2581 case CC0:
2582 if (!HAVE_cc0)
2583 gcc_unreachable ();
2584
2585 /* User of CC0 depends on immediately preceding insn. */
2586 SCHED_GROUP_P (insn) = 1;
2587 /* Don't move CC0 setter to another block (it can set up the
2588 same flag for previous CC0 users which is safe). */
2589 CANT_MOVE (prev_nonnote_insn (insn)) = 1;
2590
2591 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2592 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2593
2594 return;
2595
2596 case REG:
2597 {
2598 int regno = REGNO (x);
2599 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (x);
2600
2601 sched_analyze_reg (deps, regno, mode, USE, insn);
2602
2603#ifdef STACK_REGS
2604 /* Treat all reads of a stack register as modifying the TOS. */
2605 if (regno >= FIRST_STACK_REG && regno <= LAST_STACK_REG)
2606 {
2607 /* Avoid analyzing the same register twice. */
2608 if (regno != FIRST_STACK_REG)
2609 sched_analyze_reg (deps, FIRST_STACK_REG, mode, USE, insn);
2610 sched_analyze_reg (deps, FIRST_STACK_REG, mode, SET, insn);
2611 }
2612#endif
2613
2614 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2615 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2616
2617 return;
2618 }
2619
2620 case MEM:
2621 {
2622 /* Reading memory. */
2623 rtx_insn_list *u;
2624 rtx_insn_list *pending;
2625 rtx_expr_list *pending_mem;
2626 rtx t = x;
2627
2628 if (sched_deps_info->use_cselib)
2629 {
2630 machine_mode address_mode = get_address_mode (t);
2631
2632 t = shallow_copy_rtx (t);
2633 cselib_lookup_from_insn (XEXP (t, 0), address_mode, 1,
2634 GET_MODE (t), insn);
2635 XEXP (t, 0)
2636 = cselib_subst_to_values_from_insn (XEXP (t, 0), GET_MODE (t),
2637 insn);
2638 }
2639
2640 if (!DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
2641 {
2642 t = canon_rtx (t);
2643 pending = deps->pending_read_insns;
2644 pending_mem = deps->pending_read_mems;
2645 while (pending)
2646 {
2647 if (read_dependence (pending_mem->element (), t)
2648 && ! sched_insns_conditions_mutex_p (insn,
2649 pending->insn ()))
2650 note_mem_dep (t, pending_mem->element (),
2651 pending->insn (),
2652 DEP_ANTI);
2653
2654 pending = pending->next ();
2655 pending_mem = pending_mem->next ();
2656 }
2657
2658 pending = deps->pending_write_insns;
2659 pending_mem = deps->pending_write_mems;
2660 while (pending)
2661 {
2662 if (true_dependence (pending_mem->element (), VOIDmode, t)
2663 && ! sched_insns_conditions_mutex_p (insn,
2664 pending->insn ()))
2665 note_mem_dep (t, pending_mem->element (),
2666 pending->insn (),
2667 sched_deps_info->generate_spec_deps
2668 ? BEGIN_DATA | DEP_TRUE : DEP_TRUE);
2669
2670 pending = pending->next ();
2671 pending_mem = pending_mem->next ();
2672 }
2673
2674 for (u = deps->last_pending_memory_flush; u; u = u->next ())
2675 add_dependence (insn, u->insn (), REG_DEP_ANTI);
2676
2677 for (u = deps->pending_jump_insns; u; u = u->next ())
2678 if (deps_may_trap_p (x))
2679 {
2680 if ((sched_deps_info->generate_spec_deps)
2681 && sel_sched_p () && (spec_info->mask & BEGIN_CONTROL))
2682 {
2683 ds_t ds = set_dep_weak (DEP_ANTI, BEGIN_CONTROL,
2684 MAX_DEP_WEAK);
2685
2686 note_dep (u->insn (), ds);
2687 }
2688 else
2689 add_dependence (insn, u->insn (), REG_DEP_CONTROL);
2690 }
2691 }
2692
2693 /* Always add these dependencies to pending_reads, since
2694 this insn may be followed by a write. */
2695 if (!deps->readonly)
2696 {
2697 if ((deps->pending_read_list_length
2698 + deps->pending_write_list_length)
2699 >= MAX_PENDING_LIST_LENGTH
2700 && !DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
2701 flush_pending_lists (deps, insn, true, true);
2702 add_insn_mem_dependence (deps, true, insn, x);
2703 }
2704
2705 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (x, 0), insn);
2706
2707 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2708 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2709
2710 return;
2711 }
2712
2713 /* Force pending stores to memory in case a trap handler needs them.
2714 Also force pending loads from memory; loads and stores can segfault
2715 and the signal handler won't be triggered if the trap insn was moved
2716 above load or store insn. */
2717 case TRAP_IF:
2718 flush_pending_lists (deps, insn, true, true);
2719 break;
2720
2721 case PREFETCH:
2722 if (PREFETCH_SCHEDULE_BARRIER_P (x))
2723 reg_pending_barrier = TRUE_BARRIER;
2724 /* Prefetch insn contains addresses only. So if the prefetch
2725 address has no registers, there will be no dependencies on
2726 the prefetch insn. This is wrong with result code
2727 correctness point of view as such prefetch can be moved below
2728 a jump insn which usually generates MOVE_BARRIER preventing
2729 to move insns containing registers or memories through the
2730 barrier. It is also wrong with generated code performance
2731 point of view as prefetch withouth dependecies will have a
2732 tendency to be issued later instead of earlier. It is hard
2733 to generate accurate dependencies for prefetch insns as
2734 prefetch has only the start address but it is better to have
2735 something than nothing. */
2736 if (!deps->readonly)
2737 {
2738 rtx x = gen_rtx_MEM (Pmode, XEXP (PATTERN (insn), 0));
2739 if (sched_deps_info->use_cselib)
2740 cselib_lookup_from_insn (x, Pmode, true, VOIDmode, insn);
2741 add_insn_mem_dependence (deps, true, insn, x);
2742 }
2743 break;
2744
2745 case UNSPEC_VOLATILE:
2746 flush_pending_lists (deps, insn, true, true);
2747 /* FALLTHRU */
2748
2749 case ASM_OPERANDS:
2750 case ASM_INPUT:
2751 {
2752 /* Traditional and volatile asm instructions must be considered to use
2753 and clobber all hard registers, all pseudo-registers and all of
2754 memory. So must TRAP_IF and UNSPEC_VOLATILE operations.
2755
2756 Consider for instance a volatile asm that changes the fpu rounding
2757 mode. An insn should not be moved across this even if it only uses
2758 pseudo-regs because it might give an incorrectly rounded result. */
2759 if ((code != ASM_OPERANDS || MEM_VOLATILE_P (x))
2760 && !DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
2761 reg_pending_barrier = TRUE_BARRIER;
2762
2763 /* For all ASM_OPERANDS, we must traverse the vector of input operands.
2764 We can not just fall through here since then we would be confused
2765 by the ASM_INPUT rtx inside ASM_OPERANDS, which do not indicate
2766 traditional asms unlike their normal usage. */
2767
2768 if (code == ASM_OPERANDS)
2769 {
2770 for (j = 0; j < ASM_OPERANDS_INPUT_LENGTH (x); j++)
2771 sched_analyze_2 (deps, ASM_OPERANDS_INPUT (x, j), insn);
2772
2773 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2774 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2775
2776 return;
2777 }
2778 break;
2779 }
2780
2781 case PRE_DEC:
2782 case POST_DEC:
2783 case PRE_INC:
2784 case POST_INC:
2785 /* These both read and modify the result. We must handle them as writes
2786 to get proper dependencies for following instructions. We must handle
2787 them as reads to get proper dependencies from this to previous
2788 instructions. Thus we need to pass them to both sched_analyze_1
2789 and sched_analyze_2. We must call sched_analyze_2 first in order
2790 to get the proper antecedent for the read. */
2791 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (x, 0), insn);
2792 sched_analyze_1 (deps, x, insn);
2793
2794 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2795 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2796
2797 return;
2798
2799 case POST_MODIFY:
2800 case PRE_MODIFY:
2801 /* op0 = op0 + op1 */
2802 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (x, 0), insn);
2803 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (x, 1), insn);
2804 sched_analyze_1 (deps, x, insn);
2805
2806 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2807 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2808
2809 return;
2810
2811 default:
2812 break;
2813 }
2814
2815 /* Other cases: walk the insn. */
2816 fmt = GET_RTX_FORMAT (code);
2817 for (i = GET_RTX_LENGTH (code) - 1; i >= 0; i--)
2818 {
2819 if (fmt[i] == 'e')
2820 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (x, i), insn);
2821 else if (fmt[i] == 'E')
2822 for (j = 0; j < XVECLEN (x, i); j++)
2823 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XVECEXP (x, i, j), insn);
2824 }
2825
2826 if (cslr_p && sched_deps_info->finish_rhs)
2827 sched_deps_info->finish_rhs ();
2828}
2829
2830/* Try to group two fusible insns together to prevent scheduler
2831 from scheduling them apart. */
2832
2833static void
2834sched_macro_fuse_insns (rtx_insn *insn)
2835{
2836 rtx_insn *prev;
2837
2838 if (any_condjump_p (insn))
2839 {
2840 unsigned int condreg1, condreg2;
2841 rtx cc_reg_1;
2842 targetm.fixed_condition_code_regs (&condreg1, &condreg2);
2843 cc_reg_1 = gen_rtx_REG (CCmode, condreg1);
2844 prev = prev_nonnote_nondebug_insn (insn);
2845 if (!reg_referenced_p (cc_reg_1, PATTERN (insn))
2846 || !prev
2847 || !modified_in_p (cc_reg_1, prev))
2848 return;
2849 }
2850 else
2851 {
2852 rtx insn_set = single_set (insn);
2853
2854 if (!insn_set)
2855 return;
2856
2857 prev = prev_nonnote_nondebug_insn (insn);
2858 if (!prev
2859 || !single_set (prev))
2860 return;
2861
2862 }
2863
2864 if (targetm.sched.macro_fusion_pair_p (prev, insn))
2865 SCHED_GROUP_P (insn) = 1;
2866
2867}
2868
2869/* Get the implicit reg pending clobbers for INSN and save them in TEMP. */
2870void
2871get_implicit_reg_pending_clobbers (HARD_REG_SET *temp, rtx_insn *insn)
2872{
2873 extract_insn (insn);
2874 preprocess_constraints (insn);
2875 alternative_mask preferred = get_preferred_alternatives (insn);
2876 ira_implicitly_set_insn_hard_regs (temp, preferred);
2877 AND_COMPL_HARD_REG_SET (*temp, ira_no_alloc_regs);
2878}
2879
2880/* Analyze an INSN with pattern X to find all dependencies. */
2881static void
2882sched_analyze_insn (struct deps_desc *deps, rtx x, rtx_insn *insn)
2883{
2884 RTX_CODE code = GET_CODE (x);
2885 rtx link;
2886 unsigned i;
2887 reg_set_iterator rsi;
2888
2889 if (! reload_completed)
2890 {
2891 HARD_REG_SET temp;
2892 get_implicit_reg_pending_clobbers (&temp, insn);
2893 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (implicit_reg_pending_clobbers, temp);
2894 }
2895
2896 can_start_lhs_rhs_p = (NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn)
2897 && code == SET);
2898
2899 /* Group compare and branch insns for macro-fusion. */
2900 if (targetm.sched.macro_fusion_p
2901 && targetm.sched.macro_fusion_p ())
2902 sched_macro_fuse_insns (insn);
2903
2904 if (may_trap_p (x))
2905 /* Avoid moving trapping instructions across function calls that might
2906 not always return. */
2907 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_function_call_may_noreturn,
2908 1, REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
2909
2910 /* We must avoid creating a situation in which two successors of the
2911 current block have different unwind info after scheduling. If at any
2912 point the two paths re-join this leads to incorrect unwind info. */
2913 /* ??? There are certain situations involving a forced frame pointer in
2914 which, with extra effort, we could fix up the unwind info at a later
2915 CFG join. However, it seems better to notice these cases earlier
2916 during prologue generation and avoid marking the frame pointer setup
2917 as frame-related at all. */
2918 if (RTX_FRAME_RELATED_P (insn))
2919 {
2920 /* Make sure prologue insn is scheduled before next jump. */
2921 deps->sched_before_next_jump
2922 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, deps->sched_before_next_jump);
2923
2924 /* Make sure epilogue insn is scheduled after preceding jumps. */
2925 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_pending_memory_flush, 1,
2926 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
2927 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->pending_jump_insns, 1, REG_DEP_ANTI,
2928 true);
2929 }
2930
2931 if (code == COND_EXEC)
2932 {
2933 sched_analyze_2 (deps, COND_EXEC_TEST (x), insn);
2934
2935 /* ??? Should be recording conditions so we reduce the number of
2936 false dependencies. */
2937 x = COND_EXEC_CODE (x);
2938 code = GET_CODE (x);
2939 }
2940 if (code == SET || code == CLOBBER)
2941 {
2942 sched_analyze_1 (deps, x, insn);
2943
2944 /* Bare clobber insns are used for letting life analysis, reg-stack
2945 and others know that a value is dead. Depend on the last call
2946 instruction so that reg-stack won't get confused. */
2947 if (code == CLOBBER)
2948 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_function_call, 1,
2949 REG_DEP_OUTPUT, true);
2950 }
2951 else if (code == PARALLEL)
2952 {
2953 for (i = XVECLEN (x, 0); i--;)
2954 {
2955 rtx sub = XVECEXP (x, 0, i);
2956 code = GET_CODE (sub);
2957
2958 if (code == COND_EXEC)
2959 {
2960 sched_analyze_2 (deps, COND_EXEC_TEST (sub), insn);
2961 sub = COND_EXEC_CODE (sub);
2962 code = GET_CODE (sub);
2963 }
2964 if (code == SET || code == CLOBBER)
2965 sched_analyze_1 (deps, sub, insn);
2966 else
2967 sched_analyze_2 (deps, sub, insn);
2968 }
2969 }
2970 else
2971 sched_analyze_2 (deps, x, insn);
2972
2973 /* Mark registers CLOBBERED or used by called function. */
2974 if (CALL_P (insn))
2975 {
2976 for (link = CALL_INSN_FUNCTION_USAGE (insn); link; link = XEXP (link, 1))
2977 {
2978 if (GET_CODE (XEXP (link, 0)) == CLOBBER)
2979 sched_analyze_1 (deps, XEXP (link, 0), insn);
2980 else if (GET_CODE (XEXP (link, 0)) != SET)
2981 sched_analyze_2 (deps, XEXP (link, 0), insn);
2982 }
2983 /* Don't schedule anything after a tail call, tail call needs
2984 to use at least all call-saved registers. */
2985 if (SIBLING_CALL_P (insn))
2986 reg_pending_barrier = TRUE_BARRIER;
2987 else if (find_reg_note (insn, REG_SETJMP, NULL))
2988 reg_pending_barrier = MOVE_BARRIER;
2989 }
2990
2991 if (JUMP_P (insn))
2992 {
2993 rtx_insn *next = next_nonnote_nondebug_insn (insn);
2994 if (next && BARRIER_P (next))
2995 reg_pending_barrier = MOVE_BARRIER;
2996 else
2997 {
2998 rtx_insn_list *pending;
2999 rtx_expr_list *pending_mem;
3000
3001 if (sched_deps_info->compute_jump_reg_dependencies)
3002 {
3003 (*sched_deps_info->compute_jump_reg_dependencies)
3004 (insn, reg_pending_control_uses);
3005
3006 /* Make latency of jump equal to 0 by using anti-dependence. */
3007 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_control_uses, 0, i, rsi)
3008 {
3009 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3010 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3011 false);
3012 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets,
3013 0, REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3014 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->clobbers, 0,
3015 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3016 }
3017 }
3018
3019 /* All memory writes and volatile reads must happen before the
3020 jump. Non-volatile reads must happen before the jump iff
3021 the result is needed by the above register used mask. */
3022
3023 pending = deps->pending_write_insns;
3024 pending_mem = deps->pending_write_mems;
3025 while (pending)
3026 {
3027 if (! sched_insns_conditions_mutex_p (insn, pending->insn ()))
3028 add_dependence (insn, pending->insn (),
3029 REG_DEP_OUTPUT);
3030 pending = pending->next ();
3031 pending_mem = pending_mem->next ();
3032 }
3033
3034 pending = deps->pending_read_insns;
3035 pending_mem = deps->pending_read_mems;
3036 while (pending)
3037 {
3038 if (MEM_VOLATILE_P (pending_mem->element ())
3039 && ! sched_insns_conditions_mutex_p (insn, pending->insn ()))
3040 add_dependence (insn, pending->insn (),
3041 REG_DEP_OUTPUT);
3042 pending = pending->next ();
3043 pending_mem = pending_mem->next ();
3044 }
3045
3046 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_pending_memory_flush, 1,
3047 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3048 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->pending_jump_insns, 1,
3049 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3050 }
3051 }
3052
3053 /* If this instruction can throw an exception, then moving it changes
3054 where block boundaries fall. This is mighty confusing elsewhere.
3055 Therefore, prevent such an instruction from being moved. Same for
3056 non-jump instructions that define block boundaries.
3057 ??? Unclear whether this is still necessary in EBB mode. If not,
3058 add_branch_dependences should be adjusted for RGN mode instead. */
3059 if (((CALL_P (insn) || JUMP_P (insn)) && can_throw_internal (insn))
3060 || (NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn) && control_flow_insn_p (insn)))
3061 reg_pending_barrier = MOVE_BARRIER;
3062
3063 if (sched_pressure != SCHED_PRESSURE_NONE)
3064 {
3065 setup_insn_reg_uses (deps, insn);
3066 init_insn_reg_pressure_info (insn);
3067 }
3068
3069 /* Add register dependencies for insn. */
3070 if (DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
3071 {
3072 rtx_insn *prev = deps->last_debug_insn;
3073 rtx_insn_list *u;
3074
3075 if (!deps->readonly)
3076 deps->last_debug_insn = insn;
3077
3078 if (prev)
3079 add_dependence (insn, prev, REG_DEP_ANTI);
3080
3081 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_function_call, 1,
3082 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3083
3084 if (!sel_sched_p ())
3085 for (u = deps->last_pending_memory_flush; u; u = u->next ())
3086 add_dependence (insn, u->insn (), REG_DEP_ANTI);
3087
3088 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_uses, 0, i, rsi)
3089 {
3090 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3091 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 1, REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3092 /* There's no point in making REG_DEP_CONTROL dependencies for
3093 debug insns. */
3094 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->clobbers, 1, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3095 false);
3096
3097 if (!deps->readonly)
3098 reg_last->uses = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->uses);
3099 }
3100 CLEAR_REG_SET (reg_pending_uses);
3101
3102 /* Quite often, a debug insn will refer to stuff in the
3103 previous instruction, but the reason we want this
3104 dependency here is to make sure the scheduler doesn't
3105 gratuitously move a debug insn ahead. This could dirty
3106 DF flags and cause additional analysis that wouldn't have
3107 occurred in compilation without debug insns, and such
3108 additional analysis can modify the generated code. */
3109 prev = PREV_INSN (insn);
3110
3111 if (prev && NONDEBUG_INSN_P (prev))
3112 add_dependence (insn, prev, REG_DEP_ANTI);
3113 }
3114 else
3115 {
3116 regset_head set_or_clobbered;
3117
3118 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_uses, 0, i, rsi)
3119 {
3120 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3121 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0, REG_DEP_TRUE, false);
3122 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3123 false);
3124 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->clobbers, 0, REG_DEP_TRUE,
3125 false);
3126
3127 if (!deps->readonly)
3128 {
3129 reg_last->uses = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->uses);
3130 reg_last->uses_length++;
3131 }
3132 }
3133
3134 for (i = 0; i < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER; i++)
3135 if (TEST_HARD_REG_BIT (implicit_reg_pending_uses, i))
3136 {
3137 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3138 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0, REG_DEP_TRUE, false);
3139 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets, 0,
3140 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3141 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->clobbers, 0, REG_DEP_TRUE,
3142 false);
3143
3144 if (!deps->readonly)
3145 {
3146 reg_last->uses = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->uses);
3147 reg_last->uses_length++;
3148 }
3149 }
3150
3151 if (targetm.sched.exposed_pipeline)
3152 {
3153 INIT_REG_SET (&set_or_clobbered);
3154 bitmap_ior (&set_or_clobbered, reg_pending_clobbers,
3155 reg_pending_sets);
3156 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (&set_or_clobbered, 0, i, rsi)
3157 {
3158 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3159 rtx list;
3160 for (list = reg_last->uses; list; list = XEXP (list, 1))
3161 {
3162 rtx other = XEXP (list, 0);
3163 if (INSN_CACHED_COND (other) != const_true_rtx
3164 && refers_to_regno_p (i, INSN_CACHED_COND (other)))
3165 INSN_CACHED_COND (other) = const_true_rtx;
3166 }
3167 }
3168 }
3169
3170 /* If the current insn is conditional, we can't free any
3171 of the lists. */
3172 if (sched_has_condition_p (insn))
3173 {
3174 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_clobbers, 0, i, rsi)
3175 {
3176 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3177 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0, REG_DEP_OUTPUT,
3178 false);
3179 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets, 0,
3180 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3181 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->uses, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3182 false);
3183 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->control_uses, 0,
3184 REG_DEP_CONTROL, false);
3185
3186 if (!deps->readonly)
3187 {
3188 reg_last->clobbers
3189 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->clobbers);
3190 reg_last->clobbers_length++;
3191 }
3192 }
3193 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_sets, 0, i, rsi)
3194 {
3195 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3196 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0, REG_DEP_OUTPUT,
3197 false);
3198 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets, 0,
3199 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3200 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->clobbers, 0, REG_DEP_OUTPUT,
3201 false);
3202 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->uses, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3203 false);
3204 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->control_uses, 0,
3205 REG_DEP_CONTROL, false);
3206
3207 if (!deps->readonly)
3208 reg_last->sets = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->sets);
3209 }
3210 }
3211 else
3212 {
3213 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_clobbers, 0, i, rsi)
3214 {
3215 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3216 if (reg_last->uses_length >= MAX_PENDING_LIST_LENGTH
3217 || reg_last->clobbers_length >= MAX_PENDING_LIST_LENGTH)
3218 {
3219 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->sets, 0,
3220 REG_DEP_OUTPUT, false);
3221 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3222 &reg_last->implicit_sets, 0,
3223 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3224 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->uses, 0,
3225 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3226 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3227 &reg_last->control_uses, 0,
3228 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3229 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3230 &reg_last->clobbers, 0,
3231 REG_DEP_OUTPUT, false);
3232
3233 if (!deps->readonly)
3234 {
3235 reg_last->sets = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->sets);
3236 reg_last->clobbers_length = 0;
3237 reg_last->uses_length = 0;
3238 }
3239 }
3240 else
3241 {
3242 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0, REG_DEP_OUTPUT,
3243 false);
3244 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets, 0,
3245 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3246 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->uses, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3247 false);
3248 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->control_uses, 0,
3249 REG_DEP_CONTROL, false);
3250 }
3251
3252 if (!deps->readonly)
3253 {
3254 reg_last->clobbers_length++;
3255 reg_last->clobbers
3256 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->clobbers);
3257 }
3258 }
3259 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_sets, 0, i, rsi)
3260 {
3261 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3262
3263 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->sets, 0,
3264 REG_DEP_OUTPUT, false);
3265 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3266 &reg_last->implicit_sets,
3267 0, REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3268 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->clobbers, 0,
3269 REG_DEP_OUTPUT, false);
3270 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->uses, 0,
3271 REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3272 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->control_uses, 0,
3273 REG_DEP_CONTROL, false);
3274
3275 if (!deps->readonly)
3276 {
3277 reg_last->sets = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->sets);
3278 reg_last->uses_length = 0;
3279 reg_last->clobbers_length = 0;
3280 }
3281 }
3282 }
3283 if (!deps->readonly)
3284 {
3285 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (reg_pending_control_uses, 0, i, rsi)
3286 {
3287 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3288 reg_last->control_uses
3289 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->control_uses);
3290 }
3291 }
3292 }
3293
3294 for (i = 0; i < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER; i++)
3295 if (TEST_HARD_REG_BIT (implicit_reg_pending_clobbers, i))
3296 {
3297 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3298 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3299 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->clobbers, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3300 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->uses, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI, false);
3301 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->control_uses, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3302 false);
3303
3304 if (!deps->readonly)
3305 reg_last->implicit_sets
3306 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets);
3307 }
3308
3309 if (!deps->readonly)
3310 {
3311 IOR_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, reg_pending_uses);
3312 IOR_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, reg_pending_clobbers);
3313 IOR_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, reg_pending_sets);
3314 for (i = 0; i < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER; i++)
3315 if (TEST_HARD_REG_BIT (implicit_reg_pending_uses, i)
3316 || TEST_HARD_REG_BIT (implicit_reg_pending_clobbers, i))
3317 SET_REGNO_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, i);
3318
3319 /* Set up the pending barrier found. */
3320 deps->last_reg_pending_barrier = reg_pending_barrier;
3321 }
3322
3323 CLEAR_REG_SET (reg_pending_uses);
3324 CLEAR_REG_SET (reg_pending_clobbers);
3325 CLEAR_REG_SET (reg_pending_sets);
3326 CLEAR_REG_SET (reg_pending_control_uses);
3327 CLEAR_HARD_REG_SET (implicit_reg_pending_clobbers);
3328 CLEAR_HARD_REG_SET (implicit_reg_pending_uses);
3329
3330 /* Add dependencies if a scheduling barrier was found. */
3331 if (reg_pending_barrier)
3332 {
3333 /* In the case of barrier the most added dependencies are not
3334 real, so we use anti-dependence here. */
3335 if (sched_has_condition_p (insn))
3336 {
3337 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, 0, i, rsi)
3338 {
3339 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3340 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->uses, 0, REG_DEP_ANTI,
3341 true);
3342 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->sets, 0,
3343 reg_pending_barrier == TRUE_BARRIER
3344 ? REG_DEP_TRUE : REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3345 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->implicit_sets, 0,
3346 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3347 add_dependence_list (insn, reg_last->clobbers, 0,
3348 reg_pending_barrier == TRUE_BARRIER
3349 ? REG_DEP_TRUE : REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3350 }
3351 }
3352 else
3353 {
3354 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, 0, i, rsi)
3355 {
3356 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3357 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->uses, 0,
3358 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3359 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3360 &reg_last->control_uses, 0,
3361 REG_DEP_CONTROL, true);
3362 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->sets, 0,
3363 reg_pending_barrier == TRUE_BARRIER
3364 ? REG_DEP_TRUE : REG_DEP_ANTI,
3365 true);
3366 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3367 &reg_last->implicit_sets, 0,
3368 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3369 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn, &reg_last->clobbers, 0,
3370 reg_pending_barrier == TRUE_BARRIER
3371 ? REG_DEP_TRUE : REG_DEP_ANTI,
3372 true);
3373
3374 if (!deps->readonly)
3375 {
3376 reg_last->uses_length = 0;
3377 reg_last->clobbers_length = 0;
3378 }
3379 }
3380 }
3381
3382 if (!deps->readonly)
3383 for (i = 0; i < (unsigned)deps->max_reg; i++)
3384 {
3385 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3386 reg_last->sets = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, reg_last->sets);
3387 SET_REGNO_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, i);
3388 }
3389
3390 /* Don't flush pending lists on speculative checks for
3391 selective scheduling. */
3392 if (!sel_sched_p () || !sel_insn_is_speculation_check (insn))
3393 flush_pending_lists (deps, insn, true, true);
3394
3395 reg_pending_barrier = NOT_A_BARRIER;
3396 }
3397
3398 /* If a post-call group is still open, see if it should remain so.
3399 This insn must be a simple move of a hard reg to a pseudo or
3400 vice-versa.
3401
3402 We must avoid moving these insns for correctness on targets
3403 with small register classes, and for special registers like
3404 PIC_OFFSET_TABLE_REGNUM. For simplicity, extend this to all
3405 hard regs for all targets. */
3406
3407 if (deps->in_post_call_group_p)
3408 {
3409 rtx tmp, set = single_set (insn);
3410 int src_regno, dest_regno;
3411
3412 if (set == NULL)
3413 {
3414 if (DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
3415 /* We don't want to mark debug insns as part of the same
3416 sched group. We know they really aren't, but if we use
3417 debug insns to tell that a call group is over, we'll
3418 get different code if debug insns are not there and
3419 instructions that follow seem like they should be part
3420 of the call group.
3421
3422 Also, if we did, chain_to_prev_insn would move the
3423 deps of the debug insn to the call insn, modifying
3424 non-debug post-dependency counts of the debug insn
3425 dependencies and otherwise messing with the scheduling
3426 order.
3427
3428 Instead, let such debug insns be scheduled freely, but
3429 keep the call group open in case there are insns that
3430 should be part of it afterwards. Since we grant debug
3431 insns higher priority than even sched group insns, it
3432 will all turn out all right. */
3433 goto debug_dont_end_call_group;
3434 else
3435 goto end_call_group;
3436 }
3437
3438 tmp = SET_DEST (set);
3439 if (GET_CODE (tmp) == SUBREG)
3440 tmp = SUBREG_REG (tmp);
3441 if (REG_P (tmp))
3442 dest_regno = REGNO (tmp);
3443 else
3444 goto end_call_group;
3445
3446 tmp = SET_SRC (set);
3447 if (GET_CODE (tmp) == SUBREG)
3448 tmp = SUBREG_REG (tmp);
3449 if ((GET_CODE (tmp) == PLUS
3450 || GET_CODE (tmp) == MINUS)
3451 && REG_P (XEXP (tmp, 0))
3452 && REGNO (XEXP (tmp, 0)) == STACK_POINTER_REGNUM
3453 && dest_regno == STACK_POINTER_REGNUM)
3454 src_regno = STACK_POINTER_REGNUM;
3455 else if (REG_P (tmp))
3456 src_regno = REGNO (tmp);
3457 else
3458 goto end_call_group;
3459
3460 if (src_regno < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER
3461 || dest_regno < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER)
3462 {
3463 if (!deps->readonly
3464 && deps->in_post_call_group_p == post_call_initial)
3465 deps->in_post_call_group_p = post_call;
3466
3467 if (!sel_sched_p () || sched_emulate_haifa_p)
3468 {
3469 SCHED_GROUP_P (insn) = 1;
3470 CANT_MOVE (insn) = 1;
3471 }
3472 }
3473 else
3474 {
3475 end_call_group:
3476 if (!deps->readonly)
3477 deps->in_post_call_group_p = not_post_call;
3478 }
3479 }
3480
3481 debug_dont_end_call_group:
3482 if ((current_sched_info->flags & DO_SPECULATION)
3483 && !sched_insn_is_legitimate_for_speculation_p (insn, 0))
3484 /* INSN has an internal dependency (e.g. r14 = [r14]) and thus cannot
3485 be speculated. */
3486 {
3487 if (sel_sched_p ())
3488 sel_mark_hard_insn (insn);
3489 else
3490 {
3491 sd_iterator_def sd_it;
3492 dep_t dep;
3493
3494 for (sd_it = sd_iterator_start (insn, SD_LIST_SPEC_BACK);
3495 sd_iterator_cond (&sd_it, &dep);)
3496 change_spec_dep_to_hard (sd_it);
3497 }
3498 }
3499
3500 /* We do not yet have code to adjust REG_ARGS_SIZE, therefore we must
3501 honor their original ordering. */
3502 if (find_reg_note (insn, REG_ARGS_SIZE, NULL))
3503 {
3504 if (deps->last_args_size)
3505 add_dependence (insn, deps->last_args_size, REG_DEP_OUTPUT);
3506 if (!deps->readonly)
3507 deps->last_args_size = insn;
3508 }
3509
3510 /* We must not mix prologue and epilogue insns. See PR78029. */
3511 if (prologue_contains (insn))
3512 {
3513 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_epilogue, true, REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3514 if (!deps->readonly)
3515 {
3516 if (deps->last_logue_was_epilogue)
3517 free_INSN_LIST_list (&deps->last_prologue);
3518 deps->last_prologue = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, deps->last_prologue);
3519 deps->last_logue_was_epilogue = false;
3520 }
3521 }
3522
3523 if (epilogue_contains (insn))
3524 {
3525 add_dependence_list (insn, deps->last_prologue, true, REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3526 if (!deps->readonly)
3527 {
3528 if (!deps->last_logue_was_epilogue)
3529 free_INSN_LIST_list (&deps->last_epilogue);
3530 deps->last_epilogue = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, deps->last_epilogue);
3531 deps->last_logue_was_epilogue = true;
3532 }
3533 }
3534}
3535
3536/* Return TRUE if INSN might not always return normally (e.g. call exit,
3537 longjmp, loop forever, ...). */
3538/* FIXME: Why can't this function just use flags_from_decl_or_type and
3539 test for ECF_NORETURN? */
3540static bool
3541call_may_noreturn_p (rtx_insn *insn)
3542{
3543 rtx call;
3544
3545 /* const or pure calls that aren't looping will always return. */
3546 if (RTL_CONST_OR_PURE_CALL_P (insn)
3547 && !RTL_LOOPING_CONST_OR_PURE_CALL_P (insn))
3548 return false;
3549
3550 call = get_call_rtx_from (insn);
3551 if (call && GET_CODE (XEXP (XEXP (call, 0), 0)) == SYMBOL_REF)
3552 {
3553 rtx symbol = XEXP (XEXP (call, 0), 0);
3554 if (SYMBOL_REF_DECL (symbol)
3555 && TREE_CODE (SYMBOL_REF_DECL (symbol)) == FUNCTION_DECL)
3556 {
3557 if (DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (SYMBOL_REF_DECL (symbol))
3558 == BUILT_IN_NORMAL)
3559 switch (DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (SYMBOL_REF_DECL (symbol)))
3560 {
3561 case BUILT_IN_BCMP:
3562 case BUILT_IN_BCOPY:
3563 case BUILT_IN_BZERO:
3564 case BUILT_IN_INDEX:
3565 case BUILT_IN_MEMCHR:
3566 case BUILT_IN_MEMCMP:
3567 case BUILT_IN_MEMCPY:
3568 case BUILT_IN_MEMMOVE:
3569 case BUILT_IN_MEMPCPY:
3570 case BUILT_IN_MEMSET:
3571 case BUILT_IN_RINDEX:
3572 case BUILT_IN_STPCPY:
3573 case BUILT_IN_STPNCPY:
3574 case BUILT_IN_STRCAT:
3575 case BUILT_IN_STRCHR:
3576 case BUILT_IN_STRCMP:
3577 case BUILT_IN_STRCPY:
3578 case BUILT_IN_STRCSPN:
3579 case BUILT_IN_STRLEN:
3580 case BUILT_IN_STRNCAT:
3581 case BUILT_IN_STRNCMP:
3582 case BUILT_IN_STRNCPY:
3583 case BUILT_IN_STRPBRK:
3584 case BUILT_IN_STRRCHR:
3585 case BUILT_IN_STRSPN:
3586 case BUILT_IN_STRSTR:
3587 /* Assume certain string/memory builtins always return. */
3588 return false;
3589 default:
3590 break;
3591 }
3592 }
3593 }
3594
3595 /* For all other calls assume that they might not always return. */
3596 return true;
3597}
3598
3599/* Return true if INSN should be made dependent on the previous instruction
3600 group, and if all INSN's dependencies should be moved to the first
3601 instruction of that group. */
3602
3603static bool
3604chain_to_prev_insn_p (rtx_insn *insn)
3605{
3606 /* INSN forms a group with the previous instruction. */
3607 if (SCHED_GROUP_P (insn))
3608 return true;
3609
3610 /* If the previous instruction clobbers a register R and this one sets
3611 part of R, the clobber was added specifically to help us track the
3612 liveness of R. There's no point scheduling the clobber and leaving
3613 INSN behind, especially if we move the clobber to another block. */
3614 rtx_insn *prev = prev_nonnote_nondebug_insn (insn);
3615 if (prev
3616 && INSN_P (prev)
3617 && BLOCK_FOR_INSN (prev) == BLOCK_FOR_INSN (insn)
3618 && GET_CODE (PATTERN (prev)) == CLOBBER)
3619 {
3620 rtx x = XEXP (PATTERN (prev), 0);
3621 if (set_of (x, insn))
3622 return true;
3623 }
3624
3625 return false;
3626}
3627
3628/* Analyze INSN with DEPS as a context. */
3629void
3630deps_analyze_insn (struct deps_desc *deps, rtx_insn *insn)
3631{
3632 if (sched_deps_info->start_insn)
3633 sched_deps_info->start_insn (insn);
3634
3635 /* Record the condition for this insn. */
3636 if (NONDEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
3637 {
3638 rtx t;
3639 sched_get_condition_with_rev (insn, NULL);
3640 t = INSN_CACHED_COND (insn);
3641 INSN_COND_DEPS (insn) = NULL;
3642 if (reload_completed
3643 && (current_sched_info->flags & DO_PREDICATION)
3644 && COMPARISON_P (t)
3645 && REG_P (XEXP (t, 0))
3646 && CONSTANT_P (XEXP (t, 1)))
3647 {
3648 unsigned int regno;
3649 int nregs;
3650 rtx_insn_list *cond_deps = NULL;
3651 t = XEXP (t, 0);
3652 regno = REGNO (t);
3653 nregs = REG_NREGS (t);
3654 while (nregs-- > 0)
3655 {
3656 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[regno + nregs];
3657 cond_deps = concat_INSN_LIST (reg_last->sets, cond_deps);
3658 cond_deps = concat_INSN_LIST (reg_last->clobbers, cond_deps);
3659 cond_deps = concat_INSN_LIST (reg_last->implicit_sets, cond_deps);
3660 }
3661 INSN_COND_DEPS (insn) = cond_deps;
3662 }
3663 }
3664
3665 if (JUMP_P (insn))
3666 {
3667 /* Make each JUMP_INSN (but not a speculative check)
3668 a scheduling barrier for memory references. */
3669 if (!deps->readonly
3670 && !(sel_sched_p ()
3671 && sel_insn_is_speculation_check (insn)))
3672 {
3673 /* Keep the list a reasonable size. */
3674 if (deps->pending_flush_length++ >= MAX_PENDING_LIST_LENGTH)
3675 flush_pending_lists (deps, insn, true, true);
3676 else
3677 deps->pending_jump_insns
3678 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, deps->pending_jump_insns);
3679 }
3680
3681 /* For each insn which shouldn't cross a jump, add a dependence. */
3682 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3683 &deps->sched_before_next_jump, 1,
3684 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3685
3686 sched_analyze_insn (deps, PATTERN (insn), insn);
3687 }
3688 else if (NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn) || DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
3689 {
3690 sched_analyze_insn (deps, PATTERN (insn), insn);
3691 }
3692 else if (CALL_P (insn))
3693 {
3694 int i;
3695
3696 CANT_MOVE (insn) = 1;
3697
3698 if (find_reg_note (insn, REG_SETJMP, NULL))
3699 {
3700 /* This is setjmp. Assume that all registers, not just
3701 hard registers, may be clobbered by this call. */
3702 reg_pending_barrier = MOVE_BARRIER;
3703 }
3704 else
3705 {
3706 for (i = 0; i < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER; i++)
3707 /* A call may read and modify global register variables. */
3708 if (global_regs[i])
3709 {
3710 SET_REGNO_REG_SET (reg_pending_sets, i);
3711 SET_HARD_REG_BIT (implicit_reg_pending_uses, i);
3712 }
3713 /* Other call-clobbered hard regs may be clobbered.
3714 Since we only have a choice between 'might be clobbered'
3715 and 'definitely not clobbered', we must include all
3716 partly call-clobbered registers here. */
3717 else if (HARD_REGNO_CALL_PART_CLOBBERED (i, reg_raw_mode[i])
3718 || TEST_HARD_REG_BIT (regs_invalidated_by_call, i))
3719 SET_REGNO_REG_SET (reg_pending_clobbers, i);
3720 /* We don't know what set of fixed registers might be used
3721 by the function, but it is certain that the stack pointer
3722 is among them, but be conservative. */
3723 else if (fixed_regs[i])
3724 SET_HARD_REG_BIT (implicit_reg_pending_uses, i);
3725 /* The frame pointer is normally not used by the function
3726 itself, but by the debugger. */
3727 /* ??? MIPS o32 is an exception. It uses the frame pointer
3728 in the macro expansion of jal but does not represent this
3729 fact in the call_insn rtl. */
3730 else if (i == FRAME_POINTER_REGNUM
3731 || (i == HARD_FRAME_POINTER_REGNUM
3732 && (! reload_completed || frame_pointer_needed)))
3733 SET_HARD_REG_BIT (implicit_reg_pending_uses, i);
3734 }
3735
3736 /* For each insn which shouldn't cross a call, add a dependence
3737 between that insn and this call insn. */
3738 add_dependence_list_and_free (deps, insn,
3739 &deps->sched_before_next_call, 1,
3740 REG_DEP_ANTI, true);
3741
3742 sched_analyze_insn (deps, PATTERN (insn), insn);
3743
3744 /* If CALL would be in a sched group, then this will violate
3745 convention that sched group insns have dependencies only on the
3746 previous instruction.
3747
3748 Of course one can say: "Hey! What about head of the sched group?"
3749 And I will answer: "Basic principles (one dep per insn) are always
3750 the same." */
3751 gcc_assert (!SCHED_GROUP_P (insn));
3752
3753 /* In the absence of interprocedural alias analysis, we must flush
3754 all pending reads and writes, and start new dependencies starting
3755 from here. But only flush writes for constant calls (which may
3756 be passed a pointer to something we haven't written yet). */
3757 flush_pending_lists (deps, insn, true, ! RTL_CONST_OR_PURE_CALL_P (insn));
3758
3759 if (!deps->readonly)
3760 {
3761 /* Remember the last function call for limiting lifetimes. */
3762 free_INSN_LIST_list (&deps->last_function_call);
3763 deps->last_function_call = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, NULL_RTX);
3764
3765 if (call_may_noreturn_p (insn))
3766 {
3767 /* Remember the last function call that might not always return
3768 normally for limiting moves of trapping insns. */
3769 free_INSN_LIST_list (&deps->last_function_call_may_noreturn);
3770 deps->last_function_call_may_noreturn
3771 = alloc_INSN_LIST (insn, NULL_RTX);
3772 }
3773
3774 /* Before reload, begin a post-call group, so as to keep the
3775 lifetimes of hard registers correct. */
3776 if (! reload_completed)
3777 deps->in_post_call_group_p = post_call;
3778 }
3779 }
3780
3781 if (sched_deps_info->use_cselib)
3782 cselib_process_insn (insn);
3783
3784 if (sched_deps_info->finish_insn)
3785 sched_deps_info->finish_insn ();
3786
3787 /* Fixup the dependencies in the sched group. */
3788 if ((NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn) || JUMP_P (insn))
3789 && chain_to_prev_insn_p (insn)
3790 && !sel_sched_p ())
3791 chain_to_prev_insn (insn);
3792}
3793
3794/* Initialize DEPS for the new block beginning with HEAD. */
3795void
3796deps_start_bb (struct deps_desc *deps, rtx_insn *head)
3797{
3798 gcc_assert (!deps->readonly);
3799
3800 /* Before reload, if the previous block ended in a call, show that
3801 we are inside a post-call group, so as to keep the lifetimes of
3802 hard registers correct. */
3803 if (! reload_completed && !LABEL_P (head))
3804 {
3805 rtx_insn *insn = prev_nonnote_nondebug_insn (head);
3806
3807 if (insn && CALL_P (insn))
3808 deps->in_post_call_group_p = post_call_initial;
3809 }
3810}
3811
3812/* Analyze every insn between HEAD and TAIL inclusive, creating backward
3813 dependencies for each insn. */
3814void
3815sched_analyze (struct deps_desc *deps, rtx_insn *head, rtx_insn *tail)
3816{
3817 rtx_insn *insn;
3818
3819 if (sched_deps_info->use_cselib)
3820 cselib_init (CSELIB_RECORD_MEMORY);
3821
3822 deps_start_bb (deps, head);
3823
3824 for (insn = head;; insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3825 {
3826
3827 if (INSN_P (insn))
3828 {
3829 /* And initialize deps_lists. */
3830 sd_init_insn (insn);
3831 /* Clean up SCHED_GROUP_P which may be set by last
3832 scheduler pass. */
3833 if (SCHED_GROUP_P (insn))
3834 SCHED_GROUP_P (insn) = 0;
3835 }
3836
3837 deps_analyze_insn (deps, insn);
3838
3839 if (insn == tail)
3840 {
3841 if (sched_deps_info->use_cselib)
3842 cselib_finish ();
3843 return;
3844 }
3845 }
3846 gcc_unreachable ();
3847}
3848
3849/* Helper for sched_free_deps ().
3850 Delete INSN's (RESOLVED_P) backward dependencies. */
3851static void
3852delete_dep_nodes_in_back_deps (rtx_insn *insn, bool resolved_p)
3853{
3854 sd_iterator_def sd_it;
3855 dep_t dep;
3856 sd_list_types_def types;
3857
3858 if (resolved_p)
3859 types = SD_LIST_RES_BACK;
3860 else
3861 types = SD_LIST_BACK;
3862
3863 for (sd_it = sd_iterator_start (insn, types);
3864 sd_iterator_cond (&sd_it, &dep);)
3865 {
3866 dep_link_t link = *sd_it.linkp;
3867 dep_node_t node = DEP_LINK_NODE (link);
3868 deps_list_t back_list;
3869 deps_list_t forw_list;
3870
3871 get_back_and_forw_lists (dep, resolved_p, &back_list, &forw_list);
3872 remove_from_deps_list (link, back_list);
3873 delete_dep_node (node);
3874 }
3875}
3876
3877/* Delete (RESOLVED_P) dependencies between HEAD and TAIL together with
3878 deps_lists. */
3879void
3880sched_free_deps (rtx_insn *head, rtx_insn *tail, bool resolved_p)
3881{
3882 rtx_insn *insn;
3883 rtx_insn *next_tail = NEXT_INSN (tail);
3884
3885 /* We make two passes since some insns may be scheduled before their
3886 dependencies are resolved. */
3887 for (insn = head; insn != next_tail; insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3888 if (INSN_P (insn) && INSN_LUID (insn) > 0)
3889 {
3890 /* Clear forward deps and leave the dep_nodes to the
3891 corresponding back_deps list. */
3892 if (resolved_p)
3893 clear_deps_list (INSN_RESOLVED_FORW_DEPS (insn));
3894 else
3895 clear_deps_list (INSN_FORW_DEPS (insn));
3896 }
3897 for (insn = head; insn != next_tail; insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3898 if (INSN_P (insn) && INSN_LUID (insn) > 0)
3899 {
3900 /* Clear resolved back deps together with its dep_nodes. */
3901 delete_dep_nodes_in_back_deps (insn, resolved_p);
3902
3903 sd_finish_insn (insn);
3904 }
3905}

3958/* Free insn lists found in DEPS. */
3959
3960void
3961free_deps (struct deps_desc *deps)
3962{
3963 unsigned i;
3964 reg_set_iterator rsi;
3965
3966 /* We set max_reg to 0 when this context was already freed. */
3967 if (deps->max_reg == 0)
3968 {
3969 gcc_assert (deps->reg_last == NULL);
3970 return;
3971 }
3972 deps->max_reg = 0;
3973
3974 free_INSN_LIST_list (&deps->pending_read_insns);
3975 free_EXPR_LIST_list (&deps->pending_read_mems);
3976 free_INSN_LIST_list (&deps->pending_write_insns);
3977 free_EXPR_LIST_list (&deps->pending_write_mems);
3978 free_INSN_LIST_list (&deps->last_pending_memory_flush);
3979
3980 /* Without the EXECUTE_IF_SET, this loop is executed max_reg * nr_regions
3981 times. For a testcase with 42000 regs and 8000 small basic blocks,
3982 this loop accounted for nearly 60% (84 sec) of the total -O2 runtime. */
3983 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, 0, i, rsi)
3984 {
3985 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
3986 if (reg_last->uses)
3987 free_INSN_LIST_list (&reg_last->uses);
3988 if (reg_last->sets)
3989 free_INSN_LIST_list (&reg_last->sets);
3990 if (reg_last->implicit_sets)
3991 free_INSN_LIST_list (&reg_last->implicit_sets);
3992 if (reg_last->control_uses)
3993 free_INSN_LIST_list (&reg_last->control_uses);
3994 if (reg_last->clobbers)
3995 free_INSN_LIST_list (&reg_last->clobbers);
3996 }
3997 CLEAR_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use);
3998
3999 /* As we initialize reg_last lazily, it is possible that we didn't allocate
4000 it at all. */
4001 free (deps->reg_last);
4002 deps->reg_last = NULL;
4003
4004 deps = NULL;
4005}
4006
4007/* Remove INSN from dependence contexts DEPS. */
4008void
4009remove_from_deps (struct deps_desc *deps, rtx_insn *insn)
4010{
4011 int removed;
4012 unsigned i;
4013 reg_set_iterator rsi;
4014
4015 removed = remove_from_both_dependence_lists (insn, &deps->pending_read_insns,
4016 &deps->pending_read_mems);
4017 if (!DEBUG_INSN_P (insn))
4018 deps->pending_read_list_length -= removed;
4019 removed = remove_from_both_dependence_lists (insn, &deps->pending_write_insns,
4020 &deps->pending_write_mems);
4021 deps->pending_write_list_length -= removed;
4022
4023 removed = remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &deps->pending_jump_insns);
4024 deps->pending_flush_length -= removed;
4025 removed = remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &deps->last_pending_memory_flush);
4026 deps->pending_flush_length -= removed;
4027
4028 unsigned to_clear = -1U;
4029 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, 0, i, rsi)
4030 {
4031 if (to_clear != -1U)
4032 {
4033 CLEAR_REGNO_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, to_clear);
4034 to_clear = -1U;
4035 }
4036 struct deps_reg *reg_last = &deps->reg_last[i];
4037 if (reg_last->uses)
4038 remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &reg_last->uses);
4039 if (reg_last->sets)
4040 remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &reg_last->sets);
4041 if (reg_last->implicit_sets)
4042 remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &reg_last->implicit_sets);
4043 if (reg_last->clobbers)
4044 remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &reg_last->clobbers);
4045 if (!reg_last->uses && !reg_last->sets && !reg_last->implicit_sets
4046 && !reg_last->clobbers)
4047 to_clear = i;
4048 }
4049 if (to_clear != -1U)
4050 CLEAR_REGNO_REG_SET (&deps->reg_last_in_use, to_clear);
4051
4052 if (CALL_P (insn))
4053 {
4054 remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &deps->last_function_call);
4055 remove_from_dependence_list (insn,
4056 &deps->last_function_call_may_noreturn);
4057 }
4058 remove_from_dependence_list (insn, &deps->sched_before_next_call);
4059}

4061/* Init deps data vector. */
4062static void
4063init_deps_data_vector (void)
4064{
4065 int reserve = (sched_max_luid + 1 - h_d_i_d.length ());
4066 if (reserve > 0 && ! h_d_i_d.space (reserve))
4067 h_d_i_d.safe_grow_cleared (3 * sched_max_luid / 2);
4068}
4069
4070/* If it is profitable to use them, initialize or extend (depending on
4071 GLOBAL_P) dependency data. */
4072void
4073sched_deps_init (bool global_p)
4074{
4075 /* Average number of insns in the basic block.
4076 '+ 1' is used to make it nonzero. */
4077 int insns_in_block = sched_max_luid / n_basic_blocks_for_fn (cfun) + 1;
4078
4079 init_deps_data_vector ();
4080
4081 /* We use another caching mechanism for selective scheduling, so
4082 we don't use this one. */
4083 if (!sel_sched_p () && global_p && insns_in_block > 100 * 5)
4084 {
4085 /* ?!? We could save some memory by computing a per-region luid mapping
4086 which could reduce both the number of vectors in the cache and the
4087 size of each vector. Instead we just avoid the cache entirely unless
4088 the average number of instructions in a basic block is very high. See
4089 the comment before the declaration of true_dependency_cache for
4090 what we consider "very high". */
4091 cache_size = 0;
4092 extend_dependency_caches (sched_max_luid, true);
4093 }
4094
4095 if (global_p)
4096 {
4097 dl_pool = new object_allocator<_deps_list> ("deps_list");
4098 /* Allocate lists for one block at a time. */
4099 dn_pool = new object_allocator<_dep_node> ("dep_node");
4100 /* Allocate nodes for one block at a time. */
4101 }
4102}

4104
4105/* Create or extend (depending on CREATE_P) dependency caches to
4106 size N. */
4107void
4108extend_dependency_caches (int n, bool create_p)
4109{
4110 if (create_p || true_dependency_cache)
4111 {
4112 int i, luid = cache_size + n;
4113
4114 true_dependency_cache = XRESIZEVEC (bitmap_head, true_dependency_cache,
4115 luid);
4116 output_dependency_cache = XRESIZEVEC (bitmap_head,
4117 output_dependency_cache, luid);
4118 anti_dependency_cache = XRESIZEVEC (bitmap_head, anti_dependency_cache,
4119 luid);
4120 control_dependency_cache = XRESIZEVEC (bitmap_head, control_dependency_cache,
4121 luid);
4122
4123 if (current_sched_info->flags & DO_SPECULATION)
4124 spec_dependency_cache = XRESIZEVEC (bitmap_head, spec_dependency_cache,
4125 luid);
4126
4127 for (i = cache_size; i < luid; i++)
4128 {
4129 bitmap_initialize (&true_dependency_cache[i], 0);
4130 bitmap_initialize (&output_dependency_cache[i], 0);
4131 bitmap_initialize (&anti_dependency_cache[i], 0);
4132 bitmap_initialize (&control_dependency_cache[i], 0);
4133
4134 if (current_sched_info->flags & DO_SPECULATION)
4135 bitmap_initialize (&spec_dependency_cache[i], 0);
4136 }
4137 cache_size = luid;
4138 }
4139}

4141/* Finalize dependency information for the whole function. */
4142void
4143sched_deps_finish (void)
4144{
4145 gcc_assert (deps_pools_are_empty_p ());
4146 delete dn_pool;
4147 delete dl_pool;
4148 dn_pool = NULL;
4149 dl_pool = NULL;
4150
4151 h_d_i_d.release ();
4152 cache_size = 0;
4153
4154 if (true_dependency_cache)
4155 {
4156 int i;
4157
4158 for (i = 0; i < cache_size; i++)
4159 {
4160 bitmap_clear (&true_dependency_cache[i]);
4161 bitmap_clear (&output_dependency_cache[i]);
4162 bitmap_clear (&anti_dependency_cache[i]);
4163 bitmap_clear (&control_dependency_cache[i]);
4164
4165 if (sched_deps_info->generate_spec_deps)
4166 bitmap_clear (&spec_dependency_cache[i]);
4167 }
4168 free (true_dependency_cache);
4169 true_dependency_cache = NULL;
4170 free (output_dependency_cache);
4171 output_dependency_cache = NULL;
4172 free (anti_dependency_cache);
4173 anti_dependency_cache = NULL;
4174 free (control_dependency_cache);
4175 control_dependency_cache = NULL;
4176
4177 if (sched_deps_info->generate_spec_deps)
4178 {
4179 free (spec_dependency_cache);
4180 spec_dependency_cache = NULL;
4181 }
4182
4183 }
4184}

4224
4225/* Estimate the weakness of dependence between MEM1 and MEM2. */
4226dw_t
4227estimate_dep_weak (rtx mem1, rtx mem2)
4228{
4229 if (mem1 == mem2)
4230 /* MEMs are the same - don't speculate. */
4231 return MIN_DEP_WEAK;
4232
4233 rtx r1 = XEXP (mem1, 0);
4234 rtx r2 = XEXP (mem2, 0);
4235
4236 if (sched_deps_info->use_cselib)
4237 {
4238 /* We cannot call rtx_equal_for_cselib_p because the VALUEs might be
4239 dangling at this point, since we never preserve them. Instead we
4240 canonicalize manually to get stable VALUEs out of hashing. */
4241 if (GET_CODE (r1) == VALUE && CSELIB_VAL_PTR (r1))
4242 r1 = canonical_cselib_val (CSELIB_VAL_PTR (r1))->val_rtx;
4243 if (GET_CODE (r2) == VALUE && CSELIB_VAL_PTR (r2))
4244 r2 = canonical_cselib_val (CSELIB_VAL_PTR (r2))->val_rtx;
4245 }
4246
4247 if (r1 == r2
4248 || (REG_P (r1) && REG_P (r2) && REGNO (r1) == REGNO (r2)))
4249 /* Again, MEMs are the same. */
4250 return MIN_DEP_WEAK;
4251 else if ((REG_P (r1) && !REG_P (r2)) || (!REG_P (r1) && REG_P (r2)))
4252 /* Different addressing modes - reason to be more speculative,
4253 than usual. */
4254 return NO_DEP_WEAK - (NO_DEP_WEAK - UNCERTAIN_DEP_WEAK) / 2;
4255 else
4256 /* We can't say anything about the dependence. */
4257 return UNCERTAIN_DEP_WEAK;
4258}
4259
4260/* Add or update backward dependence between INSN and ELEM with type DEP_TYPE.
4261 This function can handle same INSN and ELEM (INSN == ELEM).
4262 It is a convenience wrapper. */
4263static void
4264add_dependence_1 (rtx_insn *insn, rtx_insn *elem, enum reg_note dep_type)
4265{
4266 ds_t ds;
4267 bool internal;
4268
4269 if (dep_type == REG_DEP_TRUE)
4270 ds = DEP_TRUE;
4271 else if (dep_type == REG_DEP_OUTPUT)
4272 ds = DEP_OUTPUT;
4273 else if (dep_type == REG_DEP_CONTROL)
4274 ds = DEP_CONTROL;
4275 else
4276 {
4277 gcc_assert (dep_type == REG_DEP_ANTI);
4278 ds = DEP_ANTI;
4279 }
4280
4281 /* When add_dependence is called from inside sched-deps.c, we expect
4282 cur_insn to be non-null. */
4283 internal = cur_insn != NULL;
4284 if (internal)
4285 gcc_assert (insn == cur_insn);
4286 else
4287 cur_insn = insn;
4288
4289 note_dep (elem, ds);
4290 if (!internal)
4291 cur_insn = NULL;
4292}
4293
4294/* Return weakness of speculative type TYPE in the dep_status DS,
4295 without checking to prevent ICEs on malformed input. */
4296static dw_t
4297get_dep_weak_1 (ds_t ds, ds_t type)
4298{
4299 ds = ds & type;
4300
4301 switch (type)
4302 {
4303 case BEGIN_DATA: ds >>= BEGIN_DATA_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4304 case BE_IN_DATA: ds >>= BE_IN_DATA_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4305 case BEGIN_CONTROL: ds >>= BEGIN_CONTROL_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4306 case BE_IN_CONTROL: ds >>= BE_IN_CONTROL_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4307 default: gcc_unreachable ();
4308 }
4309
4310 return (dw_t) ds;
4311}
4312
4313/* Return weakness of speculative type TYPE in the dep_status DS. */
4314dw_t
4315get_dep_weak (ds_t ds, ds_t type)
4316{
4317 dw_t dw = get_dep_weak_1 (ds, type);
4318
4319 gcc_assert (MIN_DEP_WEAK <= dw && dw <= MAX_DEP_WEAK);
4320 return dw;
4321}
4322
4323/* Return the dep_status, which has the same parameters as DS, except for
4324 speculative type TYPE, that will have weakness DW. */
4325ds_t
4326set_dep_weak (ds_t ds, ds_t type, dw_t dw)
4327{
4328 gcc_assert (MIN_DEP_WEAK <= dw && dw <= MAX_DEP_WEAK);
4329
4330 ds &= ~type;
4331 switch (type)
4332 {
4333 case BEGIN_DATA: ds |= ((ds_t) dw) << BEGIN_DATA_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4334 case BE_IN_DATA: ds |= ((ds_t) dw) << BE_IN_DATA_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4335 case BEGIN_CONTROL: ds |= ((ds_t) dw) << BEGIN_CONTROL_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4336 case BE_IN_CONTROL: ds |= ((ds_t) dw) << BE_IN_CONTROL_BITS_OFFSET; break;
4337 default: gcc_unreachable ();
4338 }
4339 return ds;
4340}
4341
4342/* Return the join of two dep_statuses DS1 and DS2.
4343 If MAX_P is true then choose the greater probability,
4344 otherwise multiply probabilities.
4345 This function assumes that both DS1 and DS2 contain speculative bits. */
4346static ds_t
4347ds_merge_1 (ds_t ds1, ds_t ds2, bool max_p)
4348{
4349 ds_t ds, t;
4350
4351 gcc_assert ((ds1 & SPECULATIVE) && (ds2 & SPECULATIVE));
4352
4353 ds = (ds1 & DEP_TYPES) | (ds2 & DEP_TYPES);
4354
4355 t = FIRST_SPEC_TYPE;
4356 do
4357 {
4358 if ((ds1 & t) && !(ds2 & t))
4359 ds |= ds1 & t;
4360 else if (!(ds1 & t) && (ds2 & t))
4361 ds |= ds2 & t;
4362 else if ((ds1 & t) && (ds2 & t))
4363 {
4364 dw_t dw1 = get_dep_weak (ds1, t);
4365 dw_t dw2 = get_dep_weak (ds2, t);
4366 ds_t dw;
4367
4368 if (!max_p)
4369 {
4370 dw = ((ds_t) dw1) * ((ds_t) dw2);
4371 dw /= MAX_DEP_WEAK;
4372 if (dw < MIN_DEP_WEAK)
4373 dw = MIN_DEP_WEAK;
4374 }
4375 else
4376 {
4377 if (dw1 >= dw2)
4378 dw = dw1;
4379 else
4380 dw = dw2;
4381 }
4382
4383 ds = set_dep_weak (ds, t, (dw_t) dw);
4384 }
4385
4386 if (t == LAST_SPEC_TYPE)
4387 break;
4388 t <<= SPEC_TYPE_SHIFT;
4389 }
4390 while (1);
4391
4392 return ds;
4393}
4394
4395/* Return the join of two dep_statuses DS1 and DS2.
4396 This function assumes that both DS1 and DS2 contain speculative bits. */
4397ds_t
4398ds_merge (ds_t ds1, ds_t ds2)
4399{
4400 return ds_merge_1 (ds1, ds2, false);
4401}
4402
4403/* Return the join of two dep_statuses DS1 and DS2. */
4404ds_t
4405ds_full_merge (ds_t ds, ds_t ds2, rtx mem1, rtx mem2)
4406{
4407 ds_t new_status = ds | ds2;
4408
4409 if (new_status & SPECULATIVE)
4410 {
4411 if ((ds && !(ds & SPECULATIVE))
4412 || (ds2 && !(ds2 & SPECULATIVE)))
4413 /* Then this dep can't be speculative. */
4414 new_status &= ~SPECULATIVE;
4415 else
4416 {
4417 /* Both are speculative. Merging probabilities. */
4418 if (mem1)
4419 {
4420 dw_t dw;
4421
4422 dw = estimate_dep_weak (mem1, mem2);
4423 ds = set_dep_weak (ds, BEGIN_DATA, dw);
4424 }
4425
4426 if (!ds)
4427 new_status = ds2;
4428 else if (!ds2)
4429 new_status = ds;
4430 else
4431 new_status = ds_merge (ds2, ds);
4432 }
4433 }
4434
4435 return new_status;
4436}
4437
4438/* Return the join of DS1 and DS2. Use maximum instead of multiplying
4439 probabilities. */
4440ds_t
4441ds_max_merge (ds_t ds1, ds_t ds2)
4442{
4443 if (ds1 == 0 && ds2 == 0)
4444 return 0;
4445
4446 if (ds1 == 0 && ds2 != 0)
4447 return ds2;
4448
4449 if (ds1 != 0 && ds2 == 0)
4450 return ds1;
4451
4452 return ds_merge_1 (ds1, ds2, true);
4453}
4454
4455/* Return the probability of speculation success for the speculation
4456 status DS. */
4457dw_t
4458ds_weak (ds_t ds)
4459{
4460 ds_t res = 1, dt;
4461 int n = 0;
4462
4463 dt = FIRST_SPEC_TYPE;
4464 do
4465 {
4466 if (ds & dt)
4467 {
4468 res *= (ds_t) get_dep_weak (ds, dt);
4469 n++;
4470 }
4471
4472 if (dt == LAST_SPEC_TYPE)
4473 break;
4474 dt <<= SPEC_TYPE_SHIFT;
4475 }
4476 while (1);
4477
4478 gcc_assert (n);
4479 while (--n)
4480 res /= MAX_DEP_WEAK;
4481
4482 if (res < MIN_DEP_WEAK)
4483 res = MIN_DEP_WEAK;
4484
4485 gcc_assert (res <= MAX_DEP_WEAK);
4486
4487 return (dw_t) res;
4488}
4489
4490/* Return a dep status that contains all speculation types of DS. */
4491ds_t
4492ds_get_speculation_types (ds_t ds)
4493{
4494 if (ds & BEGIN_DATA)
4495 ds |= BEGIN_DATA;
4496 if (ds & BE_IN_DATA)
4497 ds |= BE_IN_DATA;
4498 if (ds & BEGIN_CONTROL)
4499 ds |= BEGIN_CONTROL;
4500 if (ds & BE_IN_CONTROL)
4501 ds |= BE_IN_CONTROL;
4502
4503 return ds & SPECULATIVE;
4504}
4505
4506/* Return a dep status that contains maximal weakness for each speculation
4507 type present in DS. */
4508ds_t
4509ds_get_max_dep_weak (ds_t ds)
4510{
4511 if (ds & BEGIN_DATA)
4512 ds = set_dep_weak (ds, BEGIN_DATA, MAX_DEP_WEAK);
4513 if (ds & BE_IN_DATA)
4514 ds = set_dep_weak (ds, BE_IN_DATA, MAX_DEP_WEAK);
4515 if (ds & BEGIN_CONTROL)
4516 ds = set_dep_weak (ds, BEGIN_CONTROL, MAX_DEP_WEAK);
4517 if (ds & BE_IN_CONTROL)
4518 ds = set_dep_weak (ds, BE_IN_CONTROL, MAX_DEP_WEAK);
4519
4520 return ds;
4521}

4523/* Dump information about the dependence status S. */

4525dump_ds (FILE *f, ds_t s)
4526{
4527 fprintf (f, "{");
4528
4529 if (s & BEGIN_DATA)
4530 fprintf (f, "BEGIN_DATA: %d; ", get_dep_weak_1 (s, BEGIN_DATA));
4531 if (s & BE_IN_DATA)
4532 fprintf (f, "BE_IN_DATA: %d; ", get_dep_weak_1 (s, BE_IN_DATA));
4533 if (s & BEGIN_CONTROL)
4534 fprintf (f, "BEGIN_CONTROL: %d; ", get_dep_weak_1 (s, BEGIN_CONTROL));
4535 if (s & BE_IN_CONTROL)
4536 fprintf (f, "BE_IN_CONTROL: %d; ", get_dep_weak_1 (s, BE_IN_CONTROL));
4537
4538 if (s & HARD_DEP)
4539 fprintf (f, "HARD_DEP; ");
4540
4541 if (s & DEP_TRUE)
4542 fprintf (f, "DEP_TRUE; ");
4543 if (s & DEP_OUTPUT)
4544 fprintf (f, "DEP_OUTPUT; ");
4545 if (s & DEP_ANTI)
4546 fprintf (f, "DEP_ANTI; ");
4547 if (s & DEP_CONTROL)
4548 fprintf (f, "DEP_CONTROL; ");
4549
4550 fprintf (f, "}");
4551}

4560/* Verify that dependence type and status are consistent.
4561 If RELAXED_P is true, then skip dep_weakness checks. */
4562static void
4563check_dep (dep_t dep, bool relaxed_p)
4564{
4565 enum reg_note dt = DEP_TYPE (dep);
4566 ds_t ds = DEP_STATUS (dep);
4567
4568 gcc_assert (DEP_PRO (dep) != DEP_CON (dep));
4569
4570 if (!(current_sched_info->flags & USE_DEPS_LIST))
4571 {
4572 gcc_assert (ds == 0);
4573 return;
4574 }
4575
4576 /* Check that dependence type contains the same bits as the status. */
4577 if (dt == REG_DEP_TRUE)
4578 gcc_assert (ds & DEP_TRUE);
4579 else if (dt == REG_DEP_OUTPUT)
4580 gcc_assert ((ds & DEP_OUTPUT)
4581 && !(ds & DEP_TRUE));
4582 else if (dt == REG_DEP_ANTI)
4583 gcc_assert ((ds & DEP_ANTI)
4584 && !(ds & (DEP_OUTPUT | DEP_TRUE)));
4585 else
4586 gcc_assert (dt == REG_DEP_CONTROL
4587 && (ds & DEP_CONTROL)
4588 && !(ds & (DEP_OUTPUT | DEP_ANTI | DEP_TRUE)));
4589
4590 /* HARD_DEP can not appear in dep_status of a link. */
4591 gcc_assert (!(ds & HARD_DEP));
4592
4593 /* Check that dependence status is set correctly when speculation is not
4594 supported. */
4595 if (!sched_deps_info->generate_spec_deps)
4596 gcc_assert (!(ds & SPECULATIVE));
4597 else if (ds & SPECULATIVE)
4598 {
4599 if (!relaxed_p)
4600 {
4601 ds_t type = FIRST_SPEC_TYPE;
4602
4603 /* Check that dependence weakness is in proper range. */
4604 do
4605 {
4606 if (ds & type)
4607 get_dep_weak (ds, type);
4608
4609 if (type == LAST_SPEC_TYPE)
4610 break;
4611 type <<= SPEC_TYPE_SHIFT;
4612 }
4613 while (1);
4614 }
4615
4616 if (ds & BEGIN_SPEC)
4617 {
4618 /* Only true dependence can be data speculative. */
4619 if (ds & BEGIN_DATA)
4620 gcc_assert (ds & DEP_TRUE);
4621
4622 /* Control dependencies in the insn scheduler are represented by
4623 anti-dependencies, therefore only anti dependence can be
4624 control speculative. */
4625 if (ds & BEGIN_CONTROL)
4626 gcc_assert (ds & DEP_ANTI);
4627 }
4628 else
4629 {
4630 /* Subsequent speculations should resolve true dependencies. */
4631 gcc_assert ((ds & DEP_TYPES) == DEP_TRUE);
4632 }
4633
4634 /* Check that true and anti dependencies can't have other speculative
4635 statuses. */
4636 if (ds & DEP_TRUE)
4637 gcc_assert (ds & (BEGIN_DATA | BE_IN_SPEC));
4638 /* An output dependence can't be speculative at all. */
4639 gcc_assert (!(ds & DEP_OUTPUT));
4640 if (ds & DEP_ANTI)
4641 gcc_assert (ds & BEGIN_CONTROL);
4642 }
4643}
